@startuml
title Safehome Security Function State Diagram

state Startup {
  [*] --> Checking

  state Checking
  Checking : do / check everything during startup

  state ReadyToUse
  ReadyToUse : do / become ready to use if no problems found

  state Resetting
  Resetting : do / allow user to reset

  Checking --> ReadyToUse : no problems found
  Checking --> Resetting : problem during startup

  ReadyToUse --> StartMonitoring : user activates system
  Startup --> StartMonitoring : no problems during startup and system activated

  state Monitoring {
    state Normal
    Normal : do / continue monitoring if no alarms

    state AlarmActive
    AlarmActive : do / start alarm and send alerts if sensor triggered

    state FalseAlarm
    FalseAlarm : do / continue monitoring if false alarm

    state TimeEnded
    TimeEnded : do / continue monitoring if time ends

    Normal --> AlarmActive : sensor triggered
    AlarmActive --> FalseAlarm : false alarm or time ended
    FalseAlarm --> Normal
    TimeEnded --> Normal
  }

  state Password {
    state WaitingForPassword
    WaitingForPassword : do / wait for user input at any time

    state PasswordEntered
    PasswordEntered : do / check entered password

    WaitingForPassword --> PasswordEntered : password entered
    PasswordEntered --> WaitingForPassword : incorrect password or password correct and system returning to normal
  }

  StartMonitoring --> Password : alarm triggered or system turned off
  Password --> Monitoring : user enters the correct password
@enduml
